1. Yesterday, the US Bitcoin spot ETF had a net inflow of 66.34 million US dollars, with net inflows for two consecutive days;
2. Yesterday, the US Ethereum spot ETF had a net inflow of 18.11 million US dollars;
3. The ultra-high net worth investor and entrepreneur network Tiger 21 holds about 6 billion US dollars in digital currency;
4. VanEck predicts that SOL will rise to 520 US dollars by the end of the year, with a market value of 250 billion US dollars;
5. The total supply of stablecoins on the Base chain exceeds 4 billion US dollars, and USDC accounts for 91.5%;
6. Coinbase director: Kraken may know the identity of Satoshi Nakamoto, and it is recommended to delete relevant data;
7. JupiterDAO reminds again: Jupiter X account hackers are deleting posts and posting again, please do not interact with them;
8. The US SEC was sued by Empower Oversight for not disclosing cryptocurrency-related reports in a timely manner;
9. 15 states in the United States have tried to establish BTC Strategic reserve allocation, among which the North Dakota and Wyoming bills seem to have failed;
10. Brazilian lawmakers proposed a new draft bill to allow Brazilian funds to invest in cryptocurrencies;
11. USDT market value exceeded $141 billion, setting a record high;
12. Cosine: When the phishing gangs that issue CA focus on manipulating emotions to play rugby, technology is not the key point.
